verbLexeme: 1. To become big or bigger in all directions. English = expand.
2. To become larger and rounder by being filled with air or liquid, especially a part of your body. English = swell.
nominalLexeme: 1. The process of becoming larger in size. English = expansion.
2. A raised, curved shape on the surface of your body, that appears as a result of an injury or an illness. English = swelling.
